label: ཅོ་ནེ་བཀའ་འགྱུར།་པོད་སོ་གཅིག་པ།་མདོ་སྡེ་པ།་ཇ
description: The Tibetan Buddhist Canon: Kangyur |Edition: Chone Monastery| Volume Number 31 | Edition Category: Mdo sde. Custodial history: Edition of Chone Kangyur was produced under the patronage of the Chone King Makzor Gonpo. Project's chief editor was Chone Drakpa Shedrup (1675-1748). The Chone Kangyur is a “straight copy” of the LIthang Kangyur and thus belongs to the ’Phying ba stag rtse sub-line of the Tshal pa Kangyur line. History of this item is untrackable. (Unless specified, these are generally among the xylographic canonic collected works that survived the calamities of the last century's anti-religious campaighn in Russia, and happened to be a part of the present-day uncatalogued inventory of the IMBT's archive). Extent and format of original material: 1r-344v. Physical characteristics: Tibetan paper 58,0x17,5, inner frame 47,5x11,5 cm, black ink, 8 lines on page. Volume and issue number: 31.0. Editor of original material: Chone Drakpa Shedrup (1675-1748).
